    "discriminators": [
     "A short, bright, violently front-loaded impulse: near-zero attack, high crest, essentially all the energy in the first few milliseconds. Much shorter and much DRIER than any GUNS discharge, which carries an LF blast and a room tail — that is the reliable direction of the test.",
     "The impacted MATERIAL (dirt, wood, metal, a vest, a body) dominates the timbre and swamps the bullet, so spectral_centroid here is a material read, not a bullet read. That is exactly why this is narrowable and not separable: BULLETS-IMPACT vs METAL-IMPACT / WOOD-IMPACT / GORE-SPLAT is a semantic call.",
     "Against BULLETS-BY: an impact terminates in a transient, a by does not. Against BULLETS-RICOCHET: a rico has a pitched, DESCENDING tail after the strike — if a falling f0 is measurable, it is a rico."
    ],
