    "discriminators": [
     "Genuinely distinctive and worth catching: the classic old-west 'ping' is a PITCHED, DESCENDING WHINE. It carries a measurable f0 (harmonicity far above anything else in BULLETS) and a strongly NEGATIVE pitch_slope_semitones_per_second as the deflected, tumbling round sheds velocity. That falling tone is a signature nothing else in this category has.",
     "Against BULLETS-BY: both sweep downward, but a by is broadband NOISE with no f0 while a rico is a TONE. Test harmonicity.",
     "Against BULLETS-IMPACT: a rico opens with an impact transient but does not stop there — it is the pitched TAIL after the strike that defines it. No f0 and no pitch slope ⇒ plain IMPACT."
    ],
