    "discriminators": [
     "Brass casings ejecting and bouncing on the ground: a decaying train of small, very bright, inharmonic metallic ticks. Almost no energy below 200 Hz, the highest spectral centroid anywhere in GUNS or BULLETS, and several onsets as the casing bounces and settles.",
     "The loudness gate is the important one. Like GUNS-MECHANISM this is FOLEY-class and must be routed away from the firing subcategories by LEVEL before source ID is attempted: it cannot be a gunshot, because there is no blast and no low end.",
     "Against GUNS-MECHANISM: the same bright metallic ticks, but a shell drop BOUNCES and settles (a decaying multi-onset train) where a mechanism click is a single decisive action. Genuinely confusable; text decides.",
     "Per the UCS note, see GUNS-HANDLE for loading and unloading."
    ],
